name: time series
description: This course covers the fundamentals of Time Series Analysis, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model evaluation. Learn to analyze temporal data patterns and build predictive models.
topics: Introduction to Time Series|Data Preprocessing Techniques|Feature Engineering for Time Series|ARIMA and SARIMA Models|Machine Learning for Time Series|Model Evaluation Metrics|Forecasting and Prediction|Advanced Time Series Techniques

name: machine learning
description: Comprehensive introduction to machine learning algorithms and their applications. Master supervised and unsupervised learning techniques with hands-on projects.
topics: Introduction to Machine Learning|Supervised Learning Algorithms|Unsupervised Learning Techniques|Model Selection and Validation|Feature Selection and Engineering|Ensemble Methods|Deep Learning Basics|ML Project Lifecycle

name: deep learning
description: Advanced neural networks and deep learning architectures. Build and deploy state-of-the-art deep learning models for various applications.
topics: Neural Network Fundamentals|Convolutional Neural Networks|Recurrent Neural Networks|Transformer Architectures|Generative Adversarial Networks|Computer Vision Applications|Natural Language Processing|Model Optimization and Deployment

name: natural language processing
description: Understanding and processing human language using AI techniques. Learn to build applications that can understand, interpret, and generate human language.
topics: Text Preprocessing|Language Modeling|Sentiment Analysis|Named Entity Recognition|Machine Translation|Question Answering Systems|Chatbots and Conversational AI|Advanced NLP with Transformers
